{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01ALQW4eYagsRE4pFkMUxd99","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Weekly Design Sync — July 1, 2026\n2\t\n3\tMeeting with Andy Braren, Evan Jaquez, and Zack Bodnar covering evaluator demo prep, PatternFly 6 migration, and rubric methodology.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Points\n6\t\n7\t- Reviewed prototype evaluation results from the last sprint\n8\t- Andy: PatternFly 6 migration targeting Q3\n9\t- Zack raised usability testing automation progress as a question\n10\t- Action item: Evan to demo [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) next week (week of July 7)\n11\t- Agreed to use [Nielsen's 10 Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) as the base rubric for evaluations\n12\t- Next meeting agenda: revisit scoring dimensions (see [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md))\n13\t\n14\t## Related\n15\t\n16\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — Evan demoing this next week; central topic of discussion\n17\t- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — agreed as base rubric methodology\n18\t- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — scoring dimensions flagged for next meeting revisit\n19\t- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — evaluation results from last sprint discussed\n20\t- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack's prior feedback and context for this meeting\n21\t\n22\t## Sources\n23\t\n24\t- ~/second-brain/sources/weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md\n25\t- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n26\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68e7c754-26f5-4a6d-aea1-fe4bb4ab9f58","uuid":"b4c6cc46-ae22-41d1-ab29-62a1ea67a067","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:55:58.419Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md","content":"# Weekly Design Sync — July 1, 2026\n\nMeeting with Andy Braren, Evan Jaquez, and Zack Bodnar covering evaluator demo prep, PatternFly 6 migration, and rubric methodology.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Reviewed prototype evaluation results from the last sprint\n- Andy: PatternFly 6 migration targeting Q3\n- Zack raised usability testing automation progress as a question\n- Action item: Evan to demo [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) next week (week of July 7)\n- Agreed to use [Nielsen's 10 Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) as the base rubric for evaluations\n- Next meeting agenda: revisit scoring dimensions (see [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md))\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — Evan demoing this next week; central topic of discussion\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — agreed as base rubric methodology\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — scoring dimensions flagged for next meeting revisit\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — evaluation results from last sprint discussed\n- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack's prior feedback and context for this meeting\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n","numLines":26,"startLine":1,"totalLines":26}}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01Nff8P37o2LNWHjgokT3zVB", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here's what your wiki knows about usability testing:\n\n---\n\n## Direct matches\n\n**[Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md)**\nYour first internship task \u2014 applied Nielsen Norman's 10 Usability Heuristics to Kubernetes/OpenShift UI screens and compared how well Cursor, Claude Code, Gemini, and ChatGPT perform heuristic evaluation. Key finding: AI tools have a \"jagged edge\" \u2014 strong at some usability tasks, surprisingly weak at others. Deliverables are in a Google Doc and Slides deck. This research directly informs your evaluator methodology.\n\n**[UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)**\nThe 8-dimension scoring system (0\u20132 each) used to evaluate prototypes. The **Usability** dimension is explicitly grounded in Nielsen's 10 heuristics. Pass threshold is 6+ with no zeros. Evaluation is agent-restricted to prevent contamination.\n\n**[Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md)**\nYour primary shipped project. Three-phase pipeline for automated prototype usability assessment:\n- Phase 1: Extract ACs, personas, journeys from Jira\n- Phase 2: Playwright walkthroughs + consistency check\n- Phase 3: 7-dimension usability scoring using Zack Bodnar's persona overlay framework\n- Phase 4: HTML report + Google Sheet sync\n\nKey design choices: Outcomes (not Strategic Goals) as grounding criteria, one shared Playwright pass, 98% generic + 2% product-specific overlay, hint mechanism for dead-end navigation, human review tab with override buttons.\n\n---\n\n## Related context\n\n**Testing fragmentation problem** ([RH AI-First UX \u2014 June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md)): Zack flagged that multiple prototype/usability testing tools now exist across the org (Yonyi's team, your evaluator, heuristic skills). Yahav was assigned to draft a unified usability testing standard \u2014 proposal was due the following week.\n\n**Heuristic eval as Ansible pilot** ([Ansible AI Helpers Strategy \u2014 June 17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md)): The heuristic evaluation skill was selected as the first external pilot for Carbonite (Ansible's AI harness). Cate Ferman is coordinating 2-3 sessions with Ansible design and research teams to validate it before broader rollout.\n\n**Upcoming demo** ([Weekly Design Sync \u2014 July 1](weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md)): You're scheduled to demo the Evaluator Super Agent the week of July 7. The team agreed Nielsen's 10 heuristics is the canonical base rubric. Scoring dimensions are flagged for revisit at the next meeting.\n\n**Research references in the evaluator**: Avenir-UX (autonomous eval with SEQ/SUS) and UXCascade (multi-agent persona simulation, S1\u2013S4 severity ratings) informed the architecture.\n\n---\n\n## Knowledge gaps\n\n- No wiki page yet for Yahav's unified usability testing proposal (was in draft as of June 25)\n- No page documenting the specific 7 dimensions in Zack Bodnar's persona overlay framework\n- No coverage of SEQ/SUS scoring methodology (referenced but not detailed)"}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3187, "cache_read_input_tokens": 39625, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 3187, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "68e7c754-26f5-4a6d-aea1-fe4bb4ab9f58", "uuid": "175fa6d3-714c-488d-bba3-257adc6c9faf", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrkqNYHZFpLH2A7S3sJA", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:56:18.497Z"}
